headline: Bank Earnings Are Sending a Message: The Economy Isn’t That Bad
summary: Quarterly report cards from the largest, most systemically important U.S. banks brought investors and consumers welcome news this past week.  JPMorgan  Chase,  Bank of America Citigroup  and  Wells Fargo  all said their relatively low rates of consumer delinquencies, as well as debt they have written off as unrecoverable, were either about the same or looking better than a year ago.  “While there are nuances around the edges, consumer credit is primarily about the labor market,” JPMorgan Chief Financial Officer Jeremy Barnum told analysts on Tuesday.
